HEADWORD: Pourpoint
<hw>Pour"point</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety> <def>A
quilted military doublet or gambeson worn in the 14th and 15th
centuries; also, a name for the doublet of the 16th and 17th centuries
worn by civilians.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

